msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_giprobe.rst:17
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_giprobe.rst:19
msgid ""
"``GIProbe``\\ s are used to provide high-quality real-time indirect light"
" to scenes. They precompute the effect of objects that emit light and the"
" effect of static geometry to simulate the behavior of complex light in "
"real-time. ``GIProbe``\\ s need to be baked before using, however, once "
"baked, dynamic objects will receive light from them. Further, lights can "
"be fully dynamic or baked."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_giprobe.rst:21
msgid ""
"Having ``GIProbe``\\ s in a scene can be expensive, the quality of the "
"probe can be turned down in exchange for better performance in the "
":ref:`ProjectSettings <class_ProjectSettings>` using "
":ref:`ProjectSettings.rendering/quality/gi_probes/quality "
"<class_ProjectSettings_property_rendering/quality/gi_probes/quality>`."
msgstr ""

