#: ../../docs/classes/class_giprobe.rst:65
msgid ""
"**SUBDIV_64** = **0** --- Use 64 subdivisions. This is the lowest quality"
" setting, but the fastest. Use it if you can, but especially use it on "
"lower-end hardware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_giprobe.rst:67
msgid ""
"**SUBDIV_128** = **1** --- Use 128 subdivisions. This is the default "
"quality setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_giprobe.rst:69
msgid "**SUBDIV_256** = **2** --- Use 256 subdivisions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_giprobe.rst:71
msgid ""
"**SUBDIV_512** = **3** --- Use 512 subdivisions. This is the highest "
"quality setting, but the slowest. On lower-end hardware this could cause "
"the GPU to stall."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_giprobe.rst:73
msgid ""
"**SUBDIV_MAX** = **4** --- Represents the size of the :ref:`Subdiv "
"<enum_GIProbe_Subdiv>` enum."
msgstr ""

